# clui Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Build a TUI wrapper around Claude Code (via `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`) with multi-session tabs, process isolation, skills management, context tools, and git worktree support.

**Architecture:** Shell + Workers model. The shell is an Ink/React TUI (main process) that renders the three-column layout and manages UI state via Zustand. Each tab spawns an isolated worker process that runs its own Claude Agent SDK instance. Shell and workers communicate over Unix Domain Sockets (JSON protocol). SQLite stores sessions, messages, pins, snapshots, and settings.

